data.title: Retirement Party
data.text: What an amazing night! The retired guest of honor had the time of her life! Our large group ranged in age from 25-70 and EVERYONE had a blast! Amazing talent! I love live music and this is nonstop fun. Everyone was singing along, dancing ! Mike is talented and adorable and sure had a way to make my Mom ( the retiree) feel special the entire night. Thank you for memories that will last a lifetime. We will be talking about this night for a long time!

data.title: HUGE fishbowl drinks $6
data.text: This place is rad! Dueling pianos, happy hour till 8, $3 wells and $4 drafts, and fish bowl long islands... Heartburn, drunk was and great dancing- what else would you need on a Friday night? Come by if your on Mill Street, it's right by Gordon Biersch and guarantees good music and fun times!

data.title: A Tremendous Show
data.text: One of the best musical performances I've ever seen. Nonstop entertainment, all by request. The place was packed and for good reason. Definitely a club to hit with friends and coworkers.

data.title: Great fun for ALL ages!
data.text: We've been to a few dueling piano bars from Vegas to Danville to San Diego.  This bar may be in the central university district, but the crowd was diverse -- from grandparents to 40s to bridal parties. Of course by midnight it was the under 35 crowd, but no mind to us, who were ready to call it a night anyway. The piano players, who also played guitar & drums were stupendous musicians & singers. The quality of music was top notch. Unlike some piano bars we've been to, they played every one of our requests & we never paid more than $5/song. The venue is also fabulous. It's spacious with lots of seating, although to have a good view, get there before 8:30. The act is fun!  They bring the crowd into it nicely & encourage crowd/pleasing antics. Drinks are reasonable & non-smoking!  It's a little loud up front. Seems like best seats are on middle level along bar railing. We sat near stage & was fun too. You can reserve a table for $25, but catch is they'll only guarantee it until 8:30. I wouldn't sit right at the stage... too close for me. If you can't find parking, try the hotel around the corner. They only charged us $5.

data.title: So much FUN!
data.text: This place has a unique vibe and layout.  The piano players were very good and very audience-inclusive.  It made for a fun evening.

data.title: Great Piano Bar
data.text: Great piano bar. Previous piano bar that was in the exact same place, went out of business. There is a new piano bar here, all re-done, new name, new everything. Solid place ideally located in the heart of the Mill Bar District. Decent prices, performers are very entertaining. Have been here multiple times.
